<body>
<p>HP has created a series of small, simplified sample applications to help you understand and exercise the Development Platform services.</p>
<p>Each sample builds on the previous one and all source code is provided for you to build, deploy, and take apart. Each sample is provided in multiple languages.</p>
<section id="prerequisites-before-you-begin"> <title>Prerequisites - Before you begin</title>
<p>In order to download and deploy these sample applications, you must have the necessary framework installed and configured.</p>
<ul>
<li>HP Helion <tm tmtype="reg">OpenStack</tm>
          <xref href="../../commercial/GA1/1.1commercial.index.dita">cloud [version 1.1.1]
            deployed</xref>.</li>
<li>Application Lifecycle Service <xref href="devplatform.deploy-ALS.dita" >Cluster</xref> available with MySQL and RabbitMQ enabled.

<ul>
<li>You can also quickly setup a cluster in the free and publicly available Helion cloud as part of
              the <xref href="devplatform.ALS-developer-trial-quick-start.dita#topic1952" type="section"  >Quick
                Start Developer Trial</xref>: </li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Logon and password credentials for the cluster.</li>
<li>Access to the <xref href="helion/user/client/client_index.dita" >Helion command-line interface (CLI)</xref>
</li>
<li>(Optional) Access to the <xref href="devplatform.eclipse.dita" >Eclipse</xref> deployment plugin for JAVA applications.</li>
</ul>
</section>
